OL,7,FAberconwy MS Janet Finch-Saunders
OL,8,Fsaid, "It is a situation that cannot
OL,9,Fcontinue, certainly with the council
OL,10,Fcrying poverty and citing it is on the
OL,11,Fedge of bankruptcy at times.
OL,13,F"We can't have a situation where they
OL,14,Fare pouring good money after bad on a
OL,15,Fbuilding that is not fit for purpose.
OL,16,FIt doesn't fulfil any requirement for
OL,17,Fthe local authority. It was a mess
OL,18,Ffrom day one, and I would have thought
OL,19,Fthe leader and cabinet would be
OL,20,Flooking to come out of that contract
OL,21,Fbut not at the cost to taxpayers."
